                        <interp inst="t18430703-name-263" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED HULME</persName>
                  </hi>. I am assistant to Mr. Hyam, a pawnbroker, of Hamlin-place, Fulham-road. On the 15th of June, between four and six o'clock, the prisoner brought this snuff-box, and sold it to me for 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he came again on the 16th, and pledged a metal watch for 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. in the name of George Lapmore, No. 9, Queen's-gardens.</p>
